# Color Package

`package color` is the pure math layer. It must stay free of side effects.

## Hard Rules

- No `os`, `fmt.println`, or file IO imports — only `vendor:raylib` for color types, `core:math`, `core:fmt` for formatting
- No Raylib drawing calls (`rl.Draw*`) — this package never touches the screen
- No global mutable state — all state flows through `ColorState` or procedure arguments
- Fallible procedures return `(result, Error_Enum)` with a domain-specific error enum — never panics (see `odin-conventions.mdc` for error handling patterns)

## Domain Constants

Define domain-specific maximums as compile-time constants in the relevant file:

```
MAX_HARMONY :: 6   // harmony.odin
MAX_SHADES  :: 32  // shade.odin
```

## File Organization

One concern per file, mirrored by a `test_*.odin` file:

| File | Concern |
|------|---------|
| `color.odin` | `ColorState`, init, get, set |
| `hex.odin` | Hex parsing, sync, validation |
| `harmony.odin` | Harmony types and computation |
| `shade.odin` | Shade generation |
| `contrast.odin` | WCAG contrast ratios |
| `colorblind.odin` | CVD simulation matrices |
